</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Hey gang,<br />
<br />
Sorry I didn’t post about this earlier. I was waiting for the numbers to be on test server, which I thought was going to be a lot sooner then today, but anyway…<br />
<br />
The new spell parameters should put shaman heals on the same ratio that they were for Planes of Power spells:<br />
<br />
Supernal Light: 2750<br />
Nature’s Infusion: 1750<br />
Tnarg’s Mending: 1300<br />
<br />
Comparatively for HP/Second:<br />
Supernal Light:  100%<br />
Nature’s Infusion: 64%<br />
Tnarg’s Mending: 47%<br />
<br />
With the new Daluda:<br />
<br />
Holy Light: 3275<br />
Sylvan Infusion: 2100<br />
Daluda’s Mending: 1550<br />
<br />
for the same comparative HP/second as the PoP heals:<br />
Supernal Light:  100%<br />
Nature’s Infusion: 64%<br />
Daluda's Mending: 47%<br />
<br />
Likewise, the Quiescence and Breath of Trushar changes should make the HoT balance equal from PoP to Gates between Clerics and Shaman.<br />
<br />
Still looking at the slow mitigation concerns in several gates zones.<br />
<br />
Again, sorry I didn’t get this info out earlier, and for letting the bad mana cost on Breath of Trushar go live.  There’s really no excuse for that blunder.<br />
<br />
-Ryan</p>
	
	
	
	
	
