	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>That assumption is stupid. We never asked for a 1800 post AA, post healing focus. We asked for a 1800 base heal.<br />
<br />
It's the usual bargaining from SoE. You ask for something and they don't give in, because that would be admitting that we know better than them what is needed. Giving us a 1550 heal isn't even 20% better than Tnarg's and it makes sure that Clerics(for instance) come out and say "See, Shamans whined and got what they asked for!".<br />
<br />
It's a shame really. We asked for reasonable things, stop treating with us, just because you want to be stubborn. And of course from every good suggestion(including mine) you chose the easiest and just copied Tnarg's and added a little more than 19%.<br />
<br />
Things like these show me that they don't listen to the voice of reason. They don't look at numbers. They do just enough to shut up enough people and judging by the feedback from us in this thread, you bet this spell will see no upgrade. <br />
<br />
We need to stand by our point, instead of being happy with what we get, because we think they listened or care. The majority asked for a 1800 heal, they gave us a 1550 which is 250 points above Tnarg's and 250 points less than our request- Classy.<br />
<br />
Don't be satisfied so easily, people. We are NOT asking for something unreasonable, we are asking for a heal that will still be 300 points worse than the Druid heal.<br />
<br />
If you kudos them now, we are done.<br />
<br />
Edit: Started this post before Rytan posted, so I am going to add something.<br />
You're right, Rytan. Our heals will now be just as balanced as they were pre-GoD and in part this board is resonsible for making it sound as if the problems with healing only exist since GoD, when in reality they were already present in PoP and LDoN. <br />
Ever since the Slow mitigation was introduced, our heals were not effective enough, obviously, you being the spell guy, you will disagree, so I ask you to look at the numbers posted here and take the time to consider if Shaman healing was adequate back in PoP:<br />
<br />
<a href="http://forums.interealms.com/shaman/showthread.php?threadid=20192" target="_blank">http://forums.interealms.com/shaman...?threadid=20192</a><br />
<br />
I'll speak my mind and say they were NOT, thus upgrading our heals so that they match the relative power to Druid and Cleric heals as in PoP, is the wrong approach. <br />
Thanks for posting, but if you read the thread, you will see that this isn't enough and that the assumption that, just because we didn't make a huge stink during PoP, our heals were fine and thus bringing them back to how they scaled to Druid and Cleric heals is sufficient, is false.</p>
	
	
	
