	<!-- message -->
	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>Wulfbane</b><br /><i>Litgruv...<br />
Although i most times agree with what you post with this 1 statement you are basically delivering a smack in the face to the whole argument of why shaman need a direct heal.<br />
<br />
I have read countless times Shaman on this board and on the cleric board and the EQLive board saying that the only Shaman who really need a new heal are the ones past Time and countless AA's etc who want to be able to hold a group together in GoD trials.<br />
<br />
If you are at this stage of the game where you NEED (notice need not would like) and you havent got max aa's and a focus then there is something wrong and perhaps you dont NEED the heal.<br />
<br />
On this note perhaps that is why SoE have made it only 1550 base as Shaman have been saying they need an 1800 pt heal which this is with max aa and focus and SoE believe that anyone at the stage of the game where they need an 1800 heal will have max aa and focus.<br />
<br />
Wulfbane</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>Well i appreciate the difference in opinion, but i have to say, i feel your 100% wrong. Just cause i dont have focus items or max AA for healing ( working on it ) doest mean i cant hack it in GoD? Means i shouldnt get this heal?  Do you realize how elitist you just sounded my friend?<br />
<br />
I have to wonder if you know what its like to play this game unguilded.<br />
<br />
Really you seem like a nice guy and all, but i very much disagree...<br />
<br />
<br />
Beyond that, having a 1800 heal i feel is a tad low anyway. If you give us a 1800 patch then put on the focus and healing, then its where "I" personaly feel our quick heal should be.<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>Rytan_EQ</b> :<br />
<br />
Thank you very much for posting your reasons behind this. It helps understand and accept what you are doing with the spells. However i think a post AA 1800 heal isnt going to cut it. I for one dont have full AA and full focus and while im working on it, the fact is i dont. I think if you move this patch heal up to 1800 the AA and focus heal resulting from this will be much more where we needed and people like myself that are in GoD and Elemental zones, but are unguilded  can really benifiet. This patch heal will not replace a cheal of any kind. With the reuqested upgrade it will still be too small a heal and too mana insufficent to push a druid out of the main healer spot in the group. However with the new HoT i think personaly itll put us right where we need to be to be a effective healing member of the group.<br />
<br />
I think we need to look beyond ratios of progression for healing classes to fix our issue correctly.<br />
<br />
<br />
Again thank you for talking to us.</p>
	
	
	
