<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Gardeltron</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Luminary<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Nov 2000<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>On the one hand, I feel relieved that the new spells return shaman healing to the status quo achieved in PoP.  I can live with that.<br />
<br />
On the other hand, this thinking assumes two things: (1) that the status quo of PoP was adequate and (2) that GoD design is such that the PoP status quo will be sufficient to assure a role for shaman healing.  I never thought that (1) was a good assumption to make, although many who have posted on this board would disagree.  I don't know enough about GoD yet to know if assumption (2) is true, although I suspect it may not be.<br />
<br />
All in all, though, this upgrade was sorely needed and I really appreciate Rytan and Brenlo for their work in helping us out.<br />
<br />
By the way, these upgrades do return us to the unchallenged role of 3rd best healer in the game.</p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br />Quote from Flabbo's interviews of EQ developers:<br />
<br />
Devs: No one likes long fights [so no more long fight content]......But [shamans] are so good in long fights! It wouldnt be balanced to increase their short battle strength.<br />
<br />
