	<p>Rytlan.<br />
<br />
Myreal question is do you think the current ratios are good for the game.<br />
<br />
100 Cleric<br />
64 Druid<br />
47 Shaman<br />
<br />
Why such a large gap between 1 and 2?<br />
Many people are finding balance wise at the top end of the game even with new heals your still looking at requiring a cleric in every single group.<br />
Preferiblly 2 clerics.<br />
<br />
Also in other aspects of the game there isn't such a large gap.<br />
Take Melee DPS.  its not 100 rogue 64 monk for example.<br />
Take Tanks.  Its not 100 Mitigation War 64 Paladin/SK<br />
Take Slows.  Its not 100 Shaman 64 Enchanter.<br />
<br />
in almost every other area the gap is more like 80-90 for 2nd place.<br />
Enchanters slow 80% as well as shaman.<br />
<br />
Wouldn't a more uniform system be something be something like<br />
100 Cleric<br />
83 Druid<br />
66 Shaman <br />
<br />
-----------------------------------------------------------------<br />
<br />
2ndly the gap in Complete Heal line is even larger.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
