	<!-- message -->
	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>slimb</b><br /><i>Lit, <br />
<br />
Question though.  From what I'm reading, to even hack it in GoD you really need to be almost time geared (or close to it).  Otherwise you're going to run into some problems.  Not that it *can't* be done, but it definitely seems that in order to really get into the heart of GoD you need to be darn well equipped/AA'd. <br />
<br />
In short, shouldn't (or at least couldn't) it be assumed that you will have the AAs maxed in the areas that these upgrades are aimed at?<br />
<br />
I don't hunt in GoD - shoot my main is still only 62 and I'm by no means ever going to raid anything bigger than the PoJ trials heh (yes I know it's not a raid) - but I can see where the idea that you should be almost max AA'd can be assumed.</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>Well to put it simply for both of us. All that is irrelivant. The point is that a 1800 heal isnt enough to begin with. If you apply the focus and AA formula to a 1800 base quick heal, you get something right about at what we need i personaly feel. Most the tanks i group with that are only elemental flagged guilds are pushing 9k or more, so with a 1500/1800 heal your healing 1.5 percent approxamitly. Thats just 1 hit from these mobs im seeing. However a 1800/2100 will put us over the danger zone. <br />
<br />
We wont be super effective healers, but if the cleric bites it atleast we can save the group. I believe this will put us right in the healign area we need to be in. Not truly a primary healer, but someone very worth having around incase things get hairy AND someone worth having on these adventures that require 2 clerics or a druid/cleric combo.<br />
<br />
More i think about it, the more sensable it seems.</p>
	
	
	
