	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>Rytan_EQ</b><br /><i><br />
Likewise, the Quiescence and Breath of Trushar changes should make the HoT balance equal from PoP to Gates between Clerics and Shaman.<br />
<br />
Still looking at the slow mitigation concerns in several gates zones.<br />
<br />
Again, sorry I didn’t get this info out earlier, and for letting the bad mana cost on Breath of Trushar go live.  There’s really no excuse for that blunder.<br />
-Ryan</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>So he does feel our pain !<br />
<br />
 Seems like most of you dont seem to be satisfied with this upgrade, but I am sure he knew there would be quite a few of you that would say "I want more".<br />
 In all honesty, this upgrade (with AA and focus effects) would put me just over 2k in heals most of the time, which is all i was looking for, when it comes to healing.<br />
<br />
 Now if they can fix our dps to the same way it was up to PoP, I would be a very happy Shaman. Either by makeing "Balance of the Nihil" a bit more usefull so we have more time to cast our dots, or by decreasing the time it in between each tick of our dots.<br />
<br />
